<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Try it yourself</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to a content page</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      From your Drupal site, go to any news article, service page, or guide.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Find the Translate this Page widget</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Look for the "Translate this Page" section at the top of the main content area,
      near the page title.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Select a language</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Use the dropdown to choose your target language. Common UK languages appear
      first, followed by all available languages.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Click Translate</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Press the "Translate" button. The page content will be replaced with the
      translated version within a few seconds.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>View the translated page</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      A banner appears confirming the language. You can click "Show original"
      at any time to revert to English.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

